{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bf1dc1d4-3b77-4c5f-8a32-331f84d97c00","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_012T2LeVWAemrGPKp7AUmG3L","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Providing NativeAOT dump config"},"type":"function"}],"interactionId":"fac1c677-8066-4650-a1e0-2944e17d8ecf","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to configure automatic crash dump collection for a NativeAOT .NET 11 app running in Kubernetes. They have `createdump` installed at `/opt/tools/createdump`. Let me provide the necessary environment variables and pod spec changes.\n\nFor .NET NativeAOT crash dump collection, the key environment variables are:\n- `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` - enables mini dump collection on crash\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4` - full dump (MiniDumpWithFullMemory), or other types\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` - path/pattern for the dump file\n\n\n- `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath=/opt/tools/createdump` - specifies the path to createdump since NativeAOT apps don't have a runtime directory where it normally lives\n- `DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics=1` - optional, for additional diagnostics\n- `DOTNET_EnableCrashReport=1` - enables crash report generation alongside the dump\n\nFor Kubernetes deployment, I need to account for storage volumes to hold the dumps, potential resource constraints since dump files can be large, and possibly a sidecar or init container to handle them.","outputTokens":575,"requestId":"D811:283A56:350BD59:3A0D0D8:69FBF03F"},"id":"d952d06a-ad65-4418-9c13-3ee90d4b369e","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:52:11.852Z","parentId":"3678222d-a285-42bb-9157-51746b786953"}
